                         <note>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above, and sometimes below, the end of the line (throughout).</note>
                         <add>Small symbols (+) written in pencil in the left margin indicate sections of reading (ff. 48r-53r, 65r-70r, 102r-108r, etc.).</add>
